{"title":"How to watch Liège-Bastogne-Liège 2025","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/watch-liege-bastogne-liege","date":1745485891000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/watch-liege-bastogne-liege\">How to watch Liège-Bastogne-Liège 2025</a></p>\n\n<p>The final <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\">Monument</a> of spring 2025, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/liege-bastogne-liege-route-riders-and-all-you-need-to-know\">Liège-Bastogne-Liège</a>, takes place on Sunday 27th April and will be broadcast live on Eurosport and Discovery+ in the UK and Europe, Flobikes in the USA and Canada, SBS in Australia and Sky in New Zealand. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also known as La Doyenne, it’s the oldest Monument, with the men’s race first held in 1892 and the women’s race added in 2017. It wraps up the Ardennes week before the week-long stage races become the main focus of attention in the run-up to the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The men’s race is run over 259km and the women’s race 147km, with the climax of both coming on the final climbs of the Côte de la La Redoute (1.9km at 9.6%) and the Côte de la Roche-aux-Faucons (4.4km at 5.4%).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In 2024 the men’s race was won from a long-range break by Tadej Pogačar, who claimed his second career victory in the race. As for the women, Grace Brown defeated a group of A-listers to win during her farewell 2024 season.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>How to watch Liège-Bastogne-Liège 2025</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-970x647.webp\" alt=\"21/04/2024 - Liège Bastogne Liège - Liège / Liège (254,5 km) - POGACAR Tadej (UAE TEAM EMIRATES)\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBL0076-A.S.O.-Gaetan-Flamme-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Gaëtan Flamme</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Liège-Bastogne-Liège takes place on Sunday 27th April 2025 and there is a range of options to catch the action live and on demand, depending on where you live. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the old-fashioned TV, the races will be shown live on TNT Sports 4 throughout the afternoon in the UK and Ireland. The broadcast of the men’s race will start at 11:00 BST, with a finish expected just after 15:00 BST. Coverage of the women’s race will come right after on TNT Sports, with the broadcast scheduled between 15:45 and 17:15 BST.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Australia, the racing will be shown live on SBS On Demand from 20:00 AEST. In the US, the racing will be broadcast on Peacock from 6:00 EST. Across the border in Canada, however, the racing will be available to watch live on FloBikes. Otherwise, Discovery+ and MAX are showing the men’s and women’s races live and on demand in the UK, Europe and other territories. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If the race isn’t being broadcast in your country or you are travelling abroad, a VPN will allow you to hide your device’s location to access content that is normally geo-blocked. One such VPN provider is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is <a href=\"https://www.techradar.com/reviews/expressvpn\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find free to watch cycling, and costs start from around £5 per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-watch-cycling-for-less-in-the-uk\">How to watch cycling for less in the UK</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Read more:</strong> <strong><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/free-to-air-cycling\">Which countries can watch cycling for free in 2025?</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+4\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Full list of broadcasters</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-970x646.webp\" alt=\"21/04/2024 - Liège Bastogne Liège Femmes - Bastogne / Liège (152,9 km) - BROWN Grace (FDJ-SUEZ)\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-1536x1023.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-2048x1364.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-1140x759.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/20240421LBF1170-A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Billy Ceusters</figcaption></figu